message:
You walk into a busy bar. The crowd reminds you of the cantina in Mos Eisley. You notice a weary old man nursing a drink. You sit down next to him and say, 'Hey stranger, what's your story?'.

The stranger looks up at you and says, "My farm's all crawling up with those nasty bots. Tried to put up a sign to keep them out today, but they just keep coming back. No matter, I need your help with something else. I seem to be locked out of my phone, I don't know what to do."

"Maybe you should write your password down", you suggest.

"I wrote it down in my phone, but I locked myself out! Oh please tell me there's something you can do", he says, and hands you a tattered old phone. Use your browser to open it.
